---
import PlaceCard from "../components/PlaceCard";
import { places } from "../constant/places";
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout>
  <section class="text-center py-20">
    <h2 class="text-5xl font-serif font-bold tracking-wide text-[#4A3F35]">
      JAIPUR
    </h2>

    <h3 class="text-lg tracking-widest text-[#4A3F35] mt-2">THE PINK CITY</h3>

    <div
      class="max-w-3xl mx-auto mt-10 space-y-8 text-lg leading-relaxed text-[#4A3F35] px-4"
    >
      <p>
        Jaipur, the vibrant capital of Rajasthan, is famously known as the Pink
        City for its stunning pink-colored heritage buildings. Founded in 1727
        by Maharaja Sawai Jai Singh II, the city beautifully blends royal
        history with modern culture. From grand forts like Amber, Nahargarh, and
        Jaigarh to iconic landmarks such as Hawa Mahal and City Palace, Jaipur
        is a treasure of Rajput architecture, art, and tradition.
      </p>

      <p>
        The bustling bazaars of Johari Bazaar and Bapu Bazaar showcase colorful
        handicrafts, jewelry, textiles, and traditional Rajasthani artwork.
        Surrounded by the Aravalli Hills and dotted with palaces, gardens,
        lakes, and museums, Jaipur offers tourists a perfect mix of heritage,
        culture, food, and adventure.
      </p>

      <p>
        Whether you're exploring the majestic forts, enjoying traditional
        cuisine like dal-baati-churma or savoring sweets like ghewar, or taking
        a camel safari â€” Jaipur promises an unforgettable experience.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div>
    {places.map((place) => <PlaceCard {...place} />)}
  </div>
</MainLayout>
